I89. Travel and transportation: pilot programs

I11(a) T4Pilot ProgramsK._Except as otherwise prohibited by law, the Secretary of Defense may conduct pilot programs to evaluate alternative travel and transportation programs, policies, and processes for Department of Defense authorized travelers. Any such pilot program shall be designed to enhance cost savings or other efficiencies that accrue to the Government and be conducted so as to evaluate one or more of the following:

I12(1) Alternative methods for performing and reimbursing travel.

I12(2) Means for limiting the need for travel.

I12(3) Means for reducing the environmental impact of travel.

Q04

