I89. Definitions

I11In this chapter:

I12(1) The term ``dependent'', with respect to a member of a uniformed service, means_

I13(A) his spouse;

I13(B) his unmarried child (including an unmarried dependent stepchild or adopted child) under 21 years of age;

I13(C) his dependent mother or father;

I13(D) a dependent designated in official records; and

I13(E) a person determined to be dependent by the Secretary concerned, or his designee.

Q04

I12(2) The term ``missing status'' means the status of a member of a uniformed service who is officially carried or determined to be absent in a status of_

I13(A) missing;

I13(B) missing in action;

I13(C) interned in a foreign country;

I13(D) captured, beleaguered, or besieged by a hostile force; or

I13(E) detained in a foreign country against his will.

Q04

I12(3) The term ``pay and allowances'' means_

I13(A) basic pay;

I13(B) special pay;

I13(C) incentive pay;

I13(D) basic allowance for housing;

I13(E) basic allowance for subsistence; and

I13(F) station per diem allowances for not more than 90 days.

